dcterms:description: The Travel Customers dataset encompasses information about travel customers aimed at aiding a travel company in computing its churn rate. The 'Target' feature denotes customer attrition, which is used as both the classification label and the feature to be audited.
dcterms:title: Travel Customers

dcterms:creator: D. R. Cox
dcterms:description: The Adult Income dataset consists of records from the 1994 Census database, comprising 48,842 instances and 14 attributes. The 'Income' feature denotes the annual income of specific individuals, which is treated as both the classification label and the feature to be audited.
dcterms:title: Adult Income

dcterms:description: The HELOC dataset comprises 10,460 samples, each with 24 features related to anonymized information about home equity line of credit (HELOC) applications made by real homeowners. The 'RiskPerformance' feature is regarded as the classification label and the feature to be audited.
dcterms:title: HELOC
